n\/insights\/merchant-solutions-worldpay\/article\/what-is-credit-card-processing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> credit card processing <\/a>or accept payments from customers. Without it, businesses couldn\u2019t accept these kinds of payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>A payment processor isn\u2019t the same as a payment gateway<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Many individuals tend to confuse one for the other when in the real sense, payment processors and payment gateways are two entirely different aspects. However, it is important to keep in mind that both of these aspects are essential in the digital payments industry.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The primary function of a payment processor is to transmit the payment details among the important parties like payment integration services like ERP, CRM or accounting platforms, card-present payments, or phone\/email transactions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, a payment gateway is like a front office because they capture and payment details to the payment processor, which works behind the scenes. Therefore, processors ensure that they securely route payment data to all the parties involved.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>There are a lot of processes involved in payment processing<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>These payment processors are vital in helping businesses process their transactions as they engage with their customers. However, what you may not know is that there are things that happen in the background before a transaction is successful. This involves some 6 essential players:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 The client<br>\u2022 The <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/business-account\/#:~:text=Verv%E2%80%99s%20merchant%20account%20open%20the%20gateways%20to%20entrepreneurs%20of%20all%20sizes%20and%20experience%20levels%20to%20set%20their%20own%20service%20fees%20and%20instantly%20settle%20payments%20(SEPA%2C%20SWIFT).\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">merchant\/business<\/a><br>\u2022 The payment processor<br>\u2022 If not combined with the processor, the payment gateway<br>\u2022 The client\u2019s credit company\/bank<br>\u2022 The merchant\u2019s bank<br>Therefore, all these parties have to be involved before any financial services online are completed for a client to receive the \u2018transaction complete\u2019 message and the business to receive funds.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-with-low-prices.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1070\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-with-low-prices.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-with-low-prices-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/payment-processors-with-low-prices-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\"><li><strong>You can find a way to get the lowest pricing for a payment processor<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Inasmuch there is no one particular way of finding the cheapest payments solution, you can do some research. Just like wholesale prices for products, you can land wholesale options when it comes to processing rates with proper research. In most cases, they are referred to a<a href=\"https:\/\/www.kabbage.com\/resource-center\/manage\/everything-you-need-to-know-about-payment-processors\/#:~:text=How%20can%20I,called%20%E2%80%9Cinterchange%20fees.%E2%80%9D\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">s interchange fees.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, don\u2019t go asking around for interchange fees but take time to study the normal charges. You need to haggle after your research and try your best to push the price down to a level where both parties feel comfortable. However, you shouldn\u2019t take pricing as the key criteria when it comes to payment processor selection. Ensure that you consider other factors, including:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Customer support<br>\u2022 Batch processing times<br>\u2022 Funds availability time<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\"><li><strong>If you don\u2019t have enough history, you might get denied<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>When applying for a payment processor\u2019s account, chances are you might get accepted or denied. It is just like taking out a bank loan. If you lack adequate quotes history, you might get denied. Therefore, if your business is relatively new, processors might not have enough to go with to accept your application because it might feel like a risky investment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, the best thing to do is to be patient, build an extensive financial history, and try again after some time. However, if you still get declined, it might be wise to talk to your bank to find out why and let them help you resolve the issue. Sometimes it just could be a matter of clarification. If it is impossible, it might be time to consider the next best payment processor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"6\"><li><strong>There are some payment processor fees that you should know<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Fees are normal. But what you may not know is that there are different types of fees involved in any kind of digital payment system. Some of these fees are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Annual\/start-up fee<br>\u2022 Discount rate<br>\u2022 Monthly statement fee<br>\u2022 Financial transaction fee<br>\u2022 Credit card processing equipment lease charge<br>\u2022 Termination fees<br>\u2022 Chargeback fees<br>\u2022 Gateway fee for internet merchant accounts<br>\u2022 Address verification fees<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Conclusion<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>These are just some of the interesting facts you may not have known about some of the popular processors in the payments industry right now. Such knowledge is instrumental in aiding your decision to find the right partner for accepting our digital payments.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction Payment processors have changed the way the payment world operates. Many merchants are now looking to embrace the digital payments revolution in the payments industry for them to reach a wider audience, including allowing cross-border payments. This is ideal for businesses, big and small alike, to boost their growth potential by maximizing their profits [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":405,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16,23,20],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/336"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=336"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/336\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1071,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/336\/revisions\/1071"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/405"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=336"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=336"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=336"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}